Commentary: Beaten! Hossain is right on the money and serves a length ball, around off. It shapes away a bit as Ali looks to block it from the crease. It beats the outside edge.
Full now, on off. Ali blocks it from the crease.
On a length, outside off. Ali leaves it well.

Big shout for LBW! Hossain lands it outside off and gets it to come back in. Ali looks to block but gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal for LBW and it looks like a good appeal but not give. Mominul Haque does not review it. Oh, it looks like it was too high. Yup, it was quite high.
FOUR! Edged away! Short of a length, outside off. Ali slashes at it and gets the outside edge. The ball goes over the slip cordon and runs to the fence.
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Lands it on a length, outside off and shapes it away. Left alone.
Too wide outside off and left alone.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
On the pads. Shafique taps it to the leg side and thinks of a run but is sent back.
Nice and full, just outside off. A nice stride forward as Abdullah Shafique pushes it to mid off.
Khaled Ahmed digs it short, on middle. It is ducked under.
Hossain fires one wide outside off Abid leaves it alone.
On a length, just outside off. Blocked out nicely by Abid Ali.
This lands outside off and comes back in. But Abid Ali is quite comfortable in leaving it alone.

Shout for LBW! Full, on off. It comes back in sharply. Ali is stuck to the crease while looking to block and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but not given. Probably, doing down the leg side.
On a length, just outside off. Ali is aware of where the off pole is and leaves it alone.
A bit closer to the off pole this time and Abid Ali blocks it well.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, quite wide outside off. Abdullah Shafique is not interested in chasing that one.
On a length, just outside off. Blocked out.
Ahmed serves a length delivery, right on the off pole. Abdullah Shafique plays it towards point.
Full and on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique works it past mid-wicket for a couple.
Short of a length, just outside off. Nicely punched past point. The fielder chases it and keeps it down to a couple.
Fuller ball, just outside off. Abid Ali blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, just outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, lands on off and comes back in. But Abid is solid in his defence.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Worked past square leg for one.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique goes back and blocks it.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Abid Ali! Back of a length, around off. Abid Ali rocks back and punches it past point for a boundary.
Good-length delivery outside off. Abid Ali leaves it alone this time.
On a length, on off. Abid Ali gets forward and defends it comfortably.
Full ball on middle this time. Abid Ali is right forward and defends it.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over! Khaled Ahmed bowls this short and wide. Abid Ali just cuts it aerially over backward point for a boundary. Wrong line and length and rightly punished.
On a length, on middle. Abid Ali defends it to the on side.
On a length, on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! A lucky boundary this time! Good-length delivery on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes at it with soft hands. The ball kisses the outside edge of his blade and goes past in the gap through slips for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it square on the leg side for a single.
Short ball this time angling into the body. Abid Ali ducks under it.
Another short delivery on middle. Abid Ali again comfortably ducks under it.
On a length this time. On middle and leg. Turned away to the on side for a single. Three boundaries in the last two overs as these two are looking more and more comfortable.
Drifting on the pads. A length delivery and Abid Ali clips it to deep square leg for a couple.
On a length, around off. Abid Ali looks to drive but gets the bottom of his blade towards the cover fielder.
On a length, on off. Abid Ali gets back and defends it.
A length delivery on middle. Abid Ali rocks back and defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Overpitched this time and punished! Khaled Ahmed bowls this full and outside off. Abid Ali drives it through covers for another boundary. They are getting boundaries quite easily now.
On a length, on middle. Abid Ali defends it to the on side and takes a quick single.
A length delivery on off. Abid Ali defends it to the off side off the front foot.
Another length delivery around off. Abid Ali blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Abid Ali is showing his class and form early in this game! Back of a length, outside off. Abid Ali rocks back and punches it through covers for a beautiful boundary.
A length delivery, on off. Pushed towards the off side off the front foot.
On a good length, around off. Defended back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on off. Abid Ali defends it watchfully.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and defends it.
Another loopy delivery on middle. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge to point.
Shorter length outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets back and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Slightly quicker on off. Abid Ali defends it off the front foot.
Quicker in the air this time, on middle. Abid Ali defends it off the inner half of his blade towards the on side.
Slower in the air on middle. That keeps a little low. Abid Ali looks to work it towards the on side and hits it to the right of short leg.
Full and on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
Loopy ball, on leg. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Abdullah Shafique gets an inside edge on the pads.
FOUR! Quality stroke! Tossed up, on the pads. Abdullah Shafique gets low and sweeps it to the square leg fence.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out with ease.
Tossed up, just outside off. Blocked out by Ali.
Full and outside off. Ali nicely drives it past point for a couple.
Flatter ball, on off. Abid goes back in the crease and blocks it.
FOUR! Punished! Full toss and on the pads. Ali flicks it past mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up, around off. Ali gets the outside edge past slip for a single.
Loopy ball, just outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it well.
A touch shorter, on off. Abid Ali goes back and cuts it to cover.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali defends it with soft hand and gets a thick outside edge to short third man for a single.
Tossed up on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter length this time. Abdullah Shafique gets back and defends it to the on side.
Slightly quicker on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it to covers.
Full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Shorter and outside off. Cut away to point.
Full and on the pads. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Abid Ali gets forward and blocks it.
Shorter ball, on off. Abid goes back and taps it out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Cut away yet again to point.
Full and on middle. Abid Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
SIX! Glorious strike! Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique dances down the track and then lifts it nicely over the long off fence. That brings up the 50-run opening stand between these two.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and blocks it.
Flatter and on the pads. Abdullah Shafique works it past square leg for one.
Beaten! Ripper of a delivery! Loopy ball, on off. Abid is stuck to the crease while looking to block and the ball turns past the outside edge.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to mid off.
Tossed up on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it off the front foot towards covers.
Nicely tossed up again, outside off. Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.
Another loopy delivery on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up again, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it again off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Tossed up around off. Abdullah Shafique decides to leave it for turn. But the ball came with the arm and hits him on the pads. There is a loud appeal by Bangladesh but the umpire is unmoved. Shakib Al Hasan is confident and Bangladesh take the review. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball is missing the stumps. So Abdullah Shafique survives.
Shorter length around off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it off the back foot towards covers.
Shorter length around off. Pushed towards the off side.
Fuller on middle. Abid Ali turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it to backward point.
Fuller on off. Abdullah Shafique drives it to long off for a single.
An arm delivery this time. Abid Ali gets deep in his crease and manages to block it.
Fuller on off. Abid Ali defends it off the front foot.
Shorter length outside off. Abdullah Shafique chops it to point.
Tossed up on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it to the on side.
On middle and fuller again. Defended back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Abdullah Shafique drives this time towards long off for a single.
Quicker delivery on middle. Slight turn there. Abid Ali defends it comfortably onto the turf.
On middle and leg. Abid Ali defends it to the on side.
Fuller on off. Pushed to mid on.
Nicley tossed up on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to defend. The ball turns away and gets the outside edge of his blade towards third man for a couple.

OUT! BOWLED! It's an arm ball that does the trick! Taijul Islam bowls an arm ball that is quicker in the air on off. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but the ball sneaks between his blade and pads and shatters the stumps. He plays for the turn there but much to his surprise the ball comes in with the arm. Smart bowling by Taijul Islam. Bangladesh get the first breakthrough!
Tossed up on middle. Azhar Ali looks to defend it off the back foot. But gets an outside edge to point as the ball turns away sharply.
Fuller on off. Azhar Ali presses forward to defend. Gets a thick outside edge to backward point.
On leg this time. Azhar Ali looks to paddle it but gets the toe end of his blade towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali blocks it out.
Shorter length this time. Abid Ali gets back and punches it to deep cover for a couple.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali gets forward and defends it comfortably.
Fuller delivery outside off. Abid Ali drives it through covers. Mehidy Hasan runs behind it form the ring and stops it with a good dive near the fence. Two runs taken.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali blocks it out.
An arm ball this time. Defended back to the bowler.
Beaten! Comes in with the angle and lands on off and turns away. Azhar Ali is beaten as he looks to block.
Again! Tossed up, just outside off. Azhar is beaten yet again while looking to block.

NOT OUT! Tossed up, lands on off turns away a bit. Azhar Ali looks to block but is beaten. There is a big appeal for caught behind and Mominul Haque is convinced by the fielder at first slip to take the review. There is a very, very small spike on UltraEdge but nothing prominent. There is probably not enough to overturn the decision so it stays as NOT OUT!
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Azhar Ali gets down the track and works it to long on for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter, on off. Abid plays it back to the bowler.
Nicely driven to mid off for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Driven but straight towards cover.
Full and on off. Azhar Ali drives it past covers for a couple.
Loopy ball, just outside off. Ali blocks it to covers.
Flatter ball, around off. Abid looks to block but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Nicely blocked out by Abid Ali.
Full and driven to mid off by Abid Ali.
Tossed up, on off. Abid Ali blocks it off the front foot.
On off, defended.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Pushed back to the bowler by Abid.
Full and on middle. Driven to mid on.
Darted on the pads. Azhar comes down the track to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali pushes it to cover.
Shorter and punched towards short cover.
Shakib bowls it full and on off. Azhar drives it to mid off.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
This lands on off and comes back in. It stays low but Abid goes back and blocks it.
This time Abid Ali comes forward and blocks this one.
Full and on middle. Abid gets the inside edge to short fine leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Both the openers are gone and Taijul Islam has struck again! Flatter ball, around off. Abid Ali goes back to cut it but there is not much room for him to free his arms. He ends up getting the bottom edge back on the off pole and Taijul Islam is delighted with that wicket. The two overs before this were maiden and the pressure was building up. Good bowling by the hosts. This over is a wicket maiden.
Loopy ball, on off. Driven to mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Azhar drives it well.
Flatter ball, on off. Azhar Ali goes back and blocks it.
Loopy ball, around off. Azhar gets the outside edge towards point.
Full ball, on off. Blocked away.
A dot as this is pushed to short cover. The fourth maiden on the trot.
Tossed up, on off. Azam gets the outside edge while looking to block but it falls short of second slip.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Azam blocks it back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed, on middle. Babar Azam blocks it well.
Flatter ball, on off. Azam goes back and cuts it to point.
Another maiden as this is blocked off the front foot by Babar.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Azhar Ali is hit on the pads while looking to flick, There is a big appeal for LBW but the ball is likely heading down the leg stump.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out by Azhar.
Darted on middle. Azhar Ali gets the inside edge towards square leg while looking to block.
Short ball, on off. Azhar gets back to cut but ends up chopping it down on the deck. Luckily for him, it doesn't roll back on the stumps.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, around off. Azam punches it to the off side.
FOUR! Top shot! Tossed up, outside off. Azam leans into it and drives it nicely to the cover fence.
Full and pushed to cover.
Tossed up, just outside off. Azam blocks it well.
Darted on middle. Worked to the leg side.
A solid defence off the front foot to end the over.
Loopy ball, on middle. Azhar gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on middle. Ali clips it to short leg.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked.
Full and on middle. Azhar works it to mid on.
Darted on the pads. Azhar Ali clips it to square leg.
Beaten! Fuller and right on the off pole. Azhar Ali looks to block it from the crease but it turns away just enough to go past the outside edge and the off pole.
Darted on the pads. Azam works it past square leg for a couple of runs.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.

NOT OUT! Tossed up, on off. Azam drives it to mid off and takes off for a single. The fielder inflicts a direct hit at the bowler's end and it deflects. The batters take the second. The TV umpire is called in but Azam is well in.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Azam gets low and blocks it.
Full and on off. Babar gets forward and blocks it with ease. That is Lunch on Day 1!
A length ball, on off. Azhar Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball, on the pads. Azhar Ali works it to wide of mid on for a single.
FOUR! PURE CLASS! Overpitched on off. Babar Azam leans forward and drives it beautifully past mid off for a boundary. Pakistan need Babar Azam to bat long on this pitch.
On the pads and fuller. Babar Azam works it to square leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Babar Azam gets on the back foot and punches it to covers.
On a length, on off. Defended off the back foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Blocked away off the back foot.
FOUR! Azhar Ali brings out a good sweep shot. Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali gets on his knees and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Quicker on middle. Azhar Ali defends this by going deep in the crease.
Fuller on middle. Driven to mid on.
Tossed up on middle. Azhar Ali defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Azhar Ali skips down the track and blocks it. Good bowling this by Taijul Islam, he is making Azhar Ali to try someting different here. Good quality Test bowling.
Turn and bounce! But down the leg side. Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Full on leg. Babar Azam works it to square on the on side.
Tossed up on middle. Babar Azam defends this off the front foot.
Quicker on off. Babar Azam defends this out.
Fuller delivery on off. Driven to mid off for a single.
Again some good turn and bounce! Tossed up around off. Azhar Ali looks to sweep but gets beaten by the sharp turn.
Loopy ball, on off. Paddled down to fine leg for a couple.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
SIX! Pulled away! Short ball, on off. Azam rocks back and pulls it all the way over the mid-wicket fence.
Flatter ball, on off. Cut away to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Azam gets forward to block it.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Azhar works it to the leg side.
Full and on off. Azam clips it uppishly but past short leg.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Azam shuffles across and blocks it.
Loopy ball, around off. Azam drives it but the man at cover dives to stop it.
FOUR! Full and down the leg side. Azam sweeps it to the fine leg fence.
Darted on off. Ali goes back and blocks it.
Flatter ball, on off.  Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Loopy ball, around off. Ali taps it towards point.
Darted on the pads. Ali gets hit on the pads while looking to block. There is a huge appeal for LBW but it is likely sliding down leg.
Darted on the pads. Ali gets some pad on it and it goes towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Quicker around off. Azhar Ali blocks it out off the back foot.
On the pads. Azhar Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on the pads again. Azhar Ali clips it to the deep mid-wicket for a single.
Mehidy Hasan again drifts this down the leg. Babar Azam nudges it to short fine leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Pushed towards the on side off the front foot.
On the pads again. Azhar Ali works it square on the on side for a single.
Quicker on middle. Azhar Ali defends this off the front foot.

In the air....but safe! Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali dances down the track and looks to go big. But miscues. The ball goes high in the air towards extra cover but falls away from the fielders. Two runs taken in the end.
BEATEN! Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali presses forward to defend but gets beaten by sharp away turn.
Quicker and flatter on off. Defended off the back foot.
Quicker again on off. Azhar Ali blocks it out.

Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali skips down the track and drives it through covers. The fielder in the ring chases it and stops it with a dive near the fence. Good fielding there as he saves two runs for his team.
Shorter length and turning into middle and leg. Babar Azam defends this towards the on side.
Shorter length outside off. Babar Azam cuts it to point.
Tossed up on off. Babar Azam gets forward and defends it.
This is bowled down the leg side. Babar Azam looks to sweep but misses as the keeper collects it.
Fuller on off. Defended off the front foot.

FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Shorter length on leg. Babar Azam rocks back and pulls it towards backward square leg for a boundary. Mehidy Hasan is getting some turn but he needs to get his line right.
Turn and bounce again for Taijul Islam! Tosses this up on off. Azhar Ali looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as that turns away sharply.
Quicker and flatter on off. Azhar Ali blocks it out.
Shorter length on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery turned into full toss by Azhar Ali. He skips down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Shorter length, on off. Azhar Ali rocks back and pulls it to wide of mid on.
Tossed up on middle. Azhar Ali gets forward and defends it.
Loopy ball, on middle. Tapped to short leg.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Azam pushes it to the left of mid on for one.
Just a single as this is pushed to long on.
Tossed up, just outside off. Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Full on off. Pushed down to long on for one.
FOUR! Cut away! Short of a length, outside off. Azam rocks back and sends the ball racing to the cover fence.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam gets forward to block it.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Punched off the back foot to deep cover for one.
Loopy ball, on middle. Azhar comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on leg. Azam works it past short leg for one. It is uppish but the fielder is late to react and move to his right.
Flatter ball, on the pads. Turned to the leg side.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Ali gets forward to block it.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Ali works it to fine leg for one.
Full and on the pads. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali gets the outside edge but it drops short of first slip.
Full and on the pads. Worked to mid on.
Shorter ball, on off. Ali gets hit on the pads while looking to block. Actually, it looks like he got an inside edge on the pads. Appeal for LBW but not given.
A single as this is pushed to long off.
Tossed up, on off. Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter ball, on off. Worked past mid on for one.
Short ball, on off. Pulled to square leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam gets forward and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Azam comes down the track and pushes it to the bowler.
Darted on off. Worked to mid-wicket.
Full and on off. Azam gets forward and blocks it under his eyes.
Full and on off. Azhar drives it to long off for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! A brilliant effort in the deep! Tossed up, on off. Azam danced down the track but ends up slicing it towards long off. The man from mid off, Khaled Ahmed, runs backward and gets towards the ball. He puts in a dive backward and to his right in the end. He gets a hand to it but it does not stick. Boundary.
FOUR! Much better this time! Short ball, on off. Pulled away by Azam to the long on fence.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
On, middle. Defended by Babar.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tossed up, on off. Ali gets low and sweeps it to the square leg fence.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali taps it down on the deck.
Flatter ball, just outside off. Azhar Ali blocks it.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali blocks it.
Full and on off. Azhar blocks it to mid on.

Tossed up, lands on off and turns away. Azam looks to block but the ball turns and goes past the bat. The keeper takes the bails off and the TV umpire is called in. But Babar Azam has his back foot back in.
Full and on the pads. Azam works it to long on for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali blocks it off the front foot.
Short ball, outside off. Cut away to deep point for one.
Tossed up, on off. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
A single as this pushed to deep cover.
Darted on the pads. Azam works it to fine leg for a couple. 50 up for the Pakistan skipper.
Full and on the pads. Clipped to short leg.
Lands on middle and turns down the leg side. Left alone.
Tossed up, on off. Azam gets forward and blocks it.
Full and on the pads. Worked past short leg for one.
Shortish ball, on middle. Ali lets the call come to him and then works it to fine leg for one.
Tossed up on middle. Driven to long off for a single.
Slower and little shorter in the length this time. Babar Azam lets it turn and then defends it to the off side.
Darted on the pads. Azam works it to deep square leg for a couple.
Shorter length on off. Punched to covers.
Tossed up on off. Defended onto the turf.
Quicker on leg. Babar Azam defends it comfortably.
On off and middle, turning into the batter. Nudged to square leg.
Turn again but down the leg side. Azhar Ali lets it go.
On middle and leg. Turned to square leg again.
Loopy delivery on off and middle. Azhar Ali works it infront of square on the on side this time.
Good sharp turn this time! Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali looks to defend it off the front foot but gets rapped up on the pads as the ball turns in. There is a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
On middle and leg. Azhar Ali defends it comfortably this time.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam this time pushes it towards the off side and takes a single.
Back of a length, on off. Azhar Ali gets on the back foot and defends it.
Short delivery angling into the body. Azhar Ali ducks under it.
Good-length delivery on off. Azhar Ali drives but gets a leading edge towards the point region. But no damage done.
On a length, on off. Azhar Ali gets well forward this time and defends it towards the off side.
Tossed up on off. Babar Azam turns it away square on the on side.
Another loopy delivery. Babar Azam defends it to the on side.
Tossed up again. Babar Azam skips down the track and looks to hit it away but manages to only hit it back to the bowler.
On middle and leg. Defended onto the turf.
Shorter on leg. Turned to fine leg for a single. 150 up for Pakistan!
Tossed up on off. Azhar Ali defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam defends it solidly.
Back of a length and outside off. Babar Azam punches it off the back foot to deep covers for a single.
Back of a length again. Azhar Ali tries to play it on up. Gets a thick outside edge but the ball falls just short of the gully fielder.
A length ball, on off. Defended comfortably this time by Azhar Ali.
Drifting on the pads this time. Azhar Ali nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Full ball, on off. Babar Azam drives it off the toe end of his blade back to the bowler.
Full and on the pads. Worked to square leg.
Flatter ball, on off. Azam goes back and blocks it.
Full and on the pads. Worked to the leg side.
A single as this is worked to long on.
Loopy ball, around off. Ali sweeps it to the deep square leg for one.
Short ball, on leg. Pulled down to fine leg for one.
Short of a length, outside off. Babar pushes it past cover for one.
Short ball, on off. Ali gets under to duck but does so late. The ball hits his helmet.
FOUR! Nice shot! A low full toss, outside off. Ali drives it nicely to the cover fence. The fielder chasing it runs into the advertisement board and falls down.
Short ball, on off. Ali sways away from the line of the ball.
Stays low! Short again, on off. Ali looks to duck under it but it stays low. He ends up tapping it to mid on.
Full and pushed to mid off. That is Tea on Day 1.
FOUR! Boundary to start the day! Length ball, down the leg side. Azam works it on its way to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, around off. Azam puts in a stride and blocks it.
Full and on the pads. Blocked out.
On a length, just outside off. A nice defence off the front foot.
Short of a length, around off. Pushed to covers.
On a length, on off. Nicely blocked by Azam.
Back of a length, around off. Ali goes back and blocks it.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short and wide outside off. Ali rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Short of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
On a length, on middle and leg. Azhar clips it to square leg.
On a length, wide outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, on off. Worked past backward point for one.
Length ball, on middle. Worked past deep square leg for one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
Short ball, outside off. Ali sways away from the line of the ball.
Short and outside off again. Azhar leaves it.
Full and outside off. Azhar gets forward and blocks it to cover.
Good-length delivery outside off. Azam decides to leave it alone.
On a good length, on off this time. Babar Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Slightly shorter on off. Babar Azam defends this off the back foot.

Back of a length and outside off. Babar Azam rides the bounce and punches it through covers. The outfield is little slow and the batters run three as the fielder at the deep stops it inside the fence. Good running.
FOUR! Short and punished! Short ball on off. Azhar Ali gets back in his crease and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Azhar Ali gets to his fifty in style! Short ball on off again and Azhar Ali pulls this in front of square towards deep mid-wicket for another boundary. Poor bowling this by Ebadot Hossain.
On a length, on off. Azam pushes it with soft hands towards the off side and gets a single.
On a length, on off. Azhar Ali defends this off the front foot.
Back of a length, on off. Azhar Ali tries to punch it towards the off side. But gets the inner half of his blade towards mid on.
On a length and around off. Azhar Ali defends this solidly.
Good-length delivery and outside off. Azhar Ali covers the line of the ball and blocks it towards the off side.
A full ball, on middle. Azhar Ali defends this to short mid-wicket.

Shorter length and outside off. Babar Azam drives it on up through covers. Again the sluggish outfield keeps the ball away from going to the fence and the batters have again taken three here. Brilliant stuff.
On a length, on off. Azhar Ali defends this towards the off side.
Full on middle. Azhar Ali clips it to short mid-wicket.
Drifting on the pads this time. Worked to deep square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery and around off. Babar Azam defends it but the ball hits the top of his blade as there is some extra bounce off the pitch.
On a length, on off. Solidly defended towards the off side.
Good-length delivery on off. Azhar Ali defends this off the front foot.
On a length, on middle and leg. Azhar Ali works it to square leg. Some low bounce there but safely negotiated by Azhar Ali.
Good-length delivery on off. Azhar Ali defends this off the front foot solidly to start off the day.
A length ball but too wide outside the off stump. Azhar Ali leaves it alone comfortably.
Good-length delivery around off. Azhar Ali decides to leave it alone again.
Little fuller and outside off. Azhar Ali shoulders his arms. So Khaled Ahmed completes his over after a day and a half.
Shorter length on off. Babar Azam rides the bounce and defends this off the back foot towards backward point.
On a length and outside off. Azam blocks it off the front foot with soft hands towards the off side and takes a single. First run of the day.
FOUR! Azhar Ali gets the first boundary of the day! Short ball on off. Azhar Ali rocks back and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Azhar Ali blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller ball, around off. Azhar Ali leans forward and drives it to the cover fielder.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ebadot Hossain gets the wicket this time from the short ball! A short ball on off. Azhar Ali looks to pull it but the ball comes a little slow off the pitch and Azhar Ali gets the top edge. The ball goes high in the air behind the stumps and Liton Das takes an easy catch to send Azhar Ali back to the hut.
Howout: c Liton Das b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: On a length, on off. Azam blocks it off the front foot towards mid on.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Babar Azam! Overpitched on leg. Babar Azam flicks it towards backward square leg for a boundary. There are looking to score quickly here Pakistan.
On a length, on off. Defended off the front foot.
A length delivery on off. It keeps a little low. Azam defends it off the bottom of his blade.
Another length ball on off. Azam this time defends it solidly off the middle of his blade.
Fuller on off. Driven to the cover fielder.
A good-length delivery around off. Alam sways his bat away from the line off the ball at the last minute. Good leave.
A length delivery and wide outside off this time. Alam leaves it alone.
On a good length, outside off. Alam leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery around off. Alam keeps his bat away from the line of the ball.
A length delivery around off. Alam leaves it alone again.
BEATEN! A good-length delivery around off. Fawad Alam looks to defend it but the ball nips away sharply to beat the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, on middle. Azam defends this off the back foot towards the on side.
On a good length, outside off. Azam leaves it alone this time.
A length ball, on off. Defended off the back foot solidly.
A good-length delivery on off. Azam taps it off the back foot towards the off side.

OUT! LBW! Khaled Ahmed gets his first Test wicket! A length ball angling into middle and leg. Babar Azam looks to clip it away but misses. Gets hit on the pads and there is a loud appeal. The umpire raises his finger but Babar Azam reviews straightaway. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows three reds and Babar Azam has to walk back. Good start for Bangladesh. They have got both the overnight batters now.
BEATEN! In that channel of uncertainity around off. Mohammad Rizwan pokes his bat at that one but the ball nips away a little and beats the outside edge of his blade.
A good-length delivery around off. Fawad Alam looks to defend it but takes his bat away from the line of the ball at the last time. Good bowling this.
A length delivery and wide outside the off stump this time. Alam leaves it alone.
Drifting on the pads this time. Alam looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit high on the pads but down the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Fawad Alam looks to leave it at the last moment but gets the toe end off his blade and the ball goes off the bounce to the keeper.
Good-length delivery around off again. Fawad Alam leaves it alone.
A length delivery on middle. Alam pushes it to mid on and gets a single.
A full  ball, outside off. Fawad Alam leaves it alone.
Fuller again on off. Fawad Alam nicely defends this off the front foot.
A full ball, on off. Fawad Alam defends this off the front foot again.
A length ball, on off. It keeps a little low. But Alam is watchful there and blocks it towards the on side.
Good-length delivery around off. Defended back to the bowler.
A full delivery on off. Worked to short mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Pushed to point.
On a length, on off. Rizwan works it to mid-wicket.
On a length, wide outside off. Rizwan leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Left alone again.
Full and on the pads. Rizwan clips it to square leg.

NOT OUT! A good-length delivery around off. Mohammad Rizwan is rooted to his crease as he looks to defend it but misses and gets hits on the pads. Bangladesh players appeal for an LBW and the umpire obliges and raises his finger. But Mohammad Rizwan reviews and the replays roll in. The UltraEdge shows that there is a spike off his blade and the decision will be overturned. They check for caught behind but the replay shows that the ball bounced short of Liton Das.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Easy pickings. Full and down the leg side. Alam clips it to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, on off. Alam blocks it from the crease.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Worked to fine leg.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short of a length, outside off. Alam cuts it to the cover fence.
Full and on the pads. Worked past mid-wicket for a couple.
Length ball, on off. Tapped to mid on. Rizwan wants a run but is sent back. The fielder misses the shy at the bowler's end.
On a length around off. Alam chops it off the bottom of his blade towards backward point.
A good-length delivery outside off. Alam leaves it alone.

Beaten! A good-length delivery around off in that channel of uncertainty. Fawad Alam pushes his bat at the ball away from the body as the ball just misses the outside edge of his blade. Ohh...the replays show that he got a faint edge on that one. Lucky there Fawad Alam. Had Bangladesh reviewed this, they would have got their third wicket in the session!
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Rizwan flicks it past mid on for a couple.
Quick run! Full and on off. Pushed to mid on and Rizwan sets off for a single. The fielder misses his shy.
Beaten this time! A good-length delivery around off and seaming away from Fawad Alam. He pushes his bat at that one as the ball misses his blade by a whisker.
Fuller on off. Pushed to mid off this time by Fawad Alam.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Pulled away! Short of a length, outside off. Rizwan pulls it nicely to the mid-wicket fence.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, just outside off. Rizwan leans forward and pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Punished! Short of a length, outside off. Rizwan swipes it across the line. The man from deep square leg gets to his left but the ball beats him.
Short of a length, around off. Left alone.
Full and turning into Alam. He rocks back and blocks it.
Fuller on off this time. Turned away towards the on side this time.
Flatter on off. Defended off the back foot off the inner half of his blade onto the on side.
On off and slower in the air. Blocked off by Alam off the back foot.
Slower in the air on off again. Alam blocks it off the back foot but the ball is going back towards the stumps. Fawad Alam stops it with his leg. Good footwork there!
Fuller on middle. Alam pushes it towards the on side.
Fuller ball, on off. Rizwan drives it back to the bowler.
A full ball again. On middle and Rizwan drives it to mid on.
A length ball, outside off. Rizwan punches it off the back foot to point.
On a length, on off. Defended off the front foot.
A full ball this time on middle. Driven straight to mid on.
On a length, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan leaves it alone comfortably.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Turned away to short fine leg.
Fuller on off this time. Pushed to long on for a single.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Defended off the front foot towards the off side.
Tossed up again, on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Oh...sharp turn this time! Slightly shorter on length on middle. Rizwan looks to defend it but the ball turns away to beat the outside edge of his blade.
Shorter length, on off. Pushed to covers off the back foot.
On a length, on off. Defended off the back foot.
A good-length delivery around off. Alam leaves it alone.
Fuller on middle. Nudged towards the on side for a single.
On a length and around off. Defended off the front foot towards the off side.
On a length, on middle. Defended towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
A short ball this time, on off. Mohammad Rizwan gets deep in his crease and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Beaten! A full ball, on off. Mohammad Rizwan looks to sweep it but the ball turns away sharply to beat him.

NOT OUT! The decision is overturned! Tossed up on off. Mohammad Rizwan gets low and looks to sweep again but misses again. This time gets hit on the pads and Bangladesh players appeal. The umpire raises his finger but Rizwan reviews it. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball is missing the stumps. So Mohammad Rizwan survives and this is a good review by the Pakistan wicketkeeper.
Beaten! Tossed up around off. Rizwan looks to defend it but the ball turns away sharply again to beat the outside edge of his blade.
Fuller again around off. Rizwan gets across and connects the sweep this time to backward square leg for a single.
Slightly shorter of full length. Alam defends it off the inner half of his blade towards square leg.
On middle and leg. Alam defends it towards the on side.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Rizwan shows no interest in playing that.
FOUR! Beautiful stroke! Full ball, on off. Rizwan nicely drives it past mid on for a boundary.
Short of a length, on middle. Rizwan works it past square leg for one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on off. Alam comes forward to block it.
Flatter ball, around off. Rizwan looks to block but gets the outside edge to third man for a single.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Punished! Shorter ball, on leg. Rizwan nicely pulls it to the mid-wicket fence.
Full and on middle. Rizwan gets forward to block it.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on the pads. Rizwan works it past mid on for a single.
On a length, outside off. Rizwan leaves it alone.
Full ball, outside off. Rizwan comes forward and blocks it out.
Full and on off. Pushed to mid off.
Short of a length, on off. Pulled to square leg for one.
FOUR! Edged away! Full ball, around off. Alam looks to block from the crease but gets the outside edge. The ball goes past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
Full and on the pads. Worked to square leg. A fumble there allows the single and that is Lunch on Day 4!
Full and on the pads. Alam taps it to short leg.
Shorter ball, on off. Alam pulls it towards short leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Alam pushes it to mid on.
Fuller, lands on off and comes back in. Alam lets the ball turn and taps it to short fine leg for one.
Low full toss, wide outside off. Rizwan sweeps it past mid-wicket for a couple.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Rizwan goes for the sweep but gets the bottom edge towards short fine leg for one.
Short of a length, outside off. Rizwan cuts but the man at point dives to his left and stops the ball.
On a length, outside off. Left alone by Rizwan.
Length ball, around off. Rizwan puts his foot forward and blocks it.
Short now and pulled down to deep backward square leg for one. That brings up the 50-run stand between these two.
Short of a length, angling across off. Punched to covers.
Hossain bowls it fuller and wider outside off. Alam lets the keeper collect it.
Tossed up around leg. Rizwan looks to defend but misses and the ball hits his pads. There is a slight appeal but it is sliding down leg.
Shorter length, on middle. Turned away to short mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle. Rizwan blocks it off the front foot.
Slower in the air, on off. Defended watchfully again.
Quicker on off. Rizwan gets back and blocks it out.
A touch shorter around off. Pushed square on the off side.
Fuller ball, on middle. Driven off the inner half of his blade towards mid on.
On a length and outside off. Alam goes for a big booming drive but gets the inner half of his blade again to square leg for a single.

DROPPED! A short ball around leg. Mohammad Rizwan pulls but gets the top edge. The ball flies in the air towards fine leg. Taijul Islam running to his left gets to it and even puts in a dive but fails to take it. A single taken in the end. Perhaps, the low light played a role in this?
On a length, on off. Turned towards the on side for a single.
On a length. Tapped towards the off side and a quick single taken again.
A good-length delivery outside off. Alam pokes at it tentatively as the ball misses his blade.
Around leg this time. Rizwan gets on his knees and sweeps it towards backward square leg for a couple. The fielder runs to his right and dives to stop it.
Another ball drifting down the leg. Rizwan paddle-sweeps this time and gets it fine for a couple again.
Beaten! Tossed up on middle. Rizwan looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Tossed up again on middle. Rizwan defends it off the inner half of his blade square on the on side for a single.
FOUR! Fawad Alam releases the pressure with a boundary! Tossed up on off. Fawad Alam skips down the track and lifts this towards the long on fence for a boundary.
Pushed quicker on off. Defended off the front foot.
Shorter on off. Rizwan pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets a couple. Good running by both the batters.
On a length and outside off. Rizwan leaves it alone this time.
Back of a length and outside off. Rizwan pushes it off the back foot towards point.
Back of a length again, angling into off. Rizwan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and wide outside off this time. Fawad Alam just leaves it alone.
A length ball, on the pads. Flicked to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Short and punished! Shakib Al Hasan bowls this halfway down the track. Fawad Alam gets back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. You can sense that these two are looking to up the ante now.
Shorter length again, on off. Alam looks to push it away but mistimes it.
Another shorter length and turning into middle. Alam pushes it off the back foot through covers for a couple.
Shorter length but this time it keeps a little low. Alam blocks it off the bottom of his blade.
Fuller and turning in. Defended by Fawad Alam solidly.
Flatter delivery on middle. Blocked away off the back foot.
Full ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, lands on off and keeps a touch low. Rizwan blocks it well.
Full and on off. Pushed to silly mid on.
Darted on the pads. Rizwan taps it past short leg for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Alam taps it to cover.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out by Alam.
Loopy ball, around off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked away.
A nice front-foot defence by Rizwan.
Rizwan works it to mid on and takes off for a quick single.
Darted on middle. Worked to short leg.
Flatter ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Rizwan goes back and blocks it.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
FOUR! Short and punished! Alam goes back and cuts it nicely through covers for a boundary.
Full and on the pads. Alam works it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Alam comes forward and blocks it well.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, just outside off. Rizwan gets forward and blocks it.
Full and on middle. Rizwan is solid in his defence.
SIX! High and handsome! Mohammad Rizwan sees the flight and dances down the track. He gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it over long on for a maximum.
A single as this is pushed to long off. 50 up for Rizwan.
Full ball, on off. Alam stays in the crease and blocks it out.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out down the ground for one.
Length ball, on off. Tapped to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
Short ball, down the leg side. Pulled to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, just outside off. Alam blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Put away! Short of a length, outside off. Alam pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket. The fielder runs to his right and slides but the ball beats him.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Rizwan taps it to the leg side for one.
Sliding down the leg side. Alam gets no bat on it and it goes to short fine leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Cut away past covers for a couple of runs.
Full ball, lands outside off and comes back in. Alam works it to backward square leg.
Nicely driven past covers for three runs this time.
Length ball, on off. Rizwan blocks it off the front foot.
Full and on middle. Worked to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Alam blocks it from the crease.
Short of a length, outside off. Alam looks to cut but gets no bat on it.
Full ball, on off. Alam pushes it to the left of mid off for one.
Length ball, on off. Worked to the leg side by Rizwan.
Full toss, on the pads. Worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out by Alam.
Loopy ball, outside off. Tapped to mid on.
Shorter ball, outside off. Alam goes back and hits it back to the bowler.
A single as this is clipped down to long on.
Tossed up, around off. Rizwan taps it to covers.
Full and on middle. Rizwan blocks it off the front foot.
Full and outside off. Alam toe-ends back to the bowler.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and wide outside off. Alam carves it to deep cover for one. He gets to his 50 and that brings up 300 for Pakistan! And also comes the declaration! Pakistan declare at 300 for 4!
Ohh....what a delivery to start the innings! A good-length delivery around off. Shadman Islam pokes at it but the ball nips away sharply with some exra bounce to beat the outside edge of his blade.
Good-length delivery again, around off. Shadman Islam leaves it alone this time.
A length ball, on off. Defended off the front foot this time.
Lovely shape again! Angling into the batter on a length, around off. But the balls seams away sharply again and beats the outside edge of the blade again.
A short ball, on off this time. Shadman Islam ducks under it.
A good-length delivery around off. Shadman Islam plays it inside the line of the ball and lets the ball go.
Tossed up on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends this off the front foot and gets a thick edge square on the off side
A flatter delivery on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Beaten now! Another tossed up around off. Joy looks to defend it off the front foot but the ball turns away sharply to beat him.
Darted on middle. Joy defends this off the front foot off the inside half of his blade towards the on side.
Fuller on off. Driven to mid off.
On middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy turns it away staright to the short leg fielder.
Slower in the air around off. Islam blocks it off the back foot.
Angled into middle. Islam defends it towards the on side.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Another loopy delivery on off. Islam defends this off the front foot. Gets a thick outside edge behind square on the off side for the first run of the innings.

OUT! The debutant departs without troubling the scorers! Tossed up on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy skips down the track and pushes at it with hard hands. Gets a thick outside edge straight to the safe hands of Babar Azam at first slip. An early wicket for Pakistan and they have an opening here.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Sajid Khan

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, Pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller on middle. Worked away wide of mid on for a single.
Flatter and quicker on off. Defended off the back foot.
Quicker and fuller this time, Shanto defends this off the front foot.
On middle this time. Shanto defends it to the on side.
Tossed up on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends this off the front foot.
Fuller on middle. Driven back to the bowler.
Nicely tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot to silly point.
Fuller on off. Islam pushes it to mid on. There is an appeal there from the bowler as the bat is close to the pads but turned down.
Fuller on off. Defended off the front foot.
Quicker on middle. Blocked off the back foot.
Sharp turn! A tad shorter around off. Islam leaves it as the ball turns away. Mohammad Rizwan fails to collect it cleanly and the batters take a bye as the ball deflects off the gloves of Rizwan.
Fuller on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short and down the leg side. Left alone.
Full ball, on off. Shadman gets forward to block it.
Full and on the pads. Islam gets it off his pads past the diving short leg fielder. Two leg byes taken.
Shorter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Worked to leg slip on the bounce.
Flatter ball, around off. Islam goes back and blocks it out.
Full and on off. Shanto blocks it off the crease.
Loopy ball, outside off. Shanto gets the outside edge but it drops short of second slip.

FOUR! Edged away! Tossed up, on off. Shanto looks to work it away but gets the outside edge. The ball goes past the slip cordon and runs towards third man. A fielder chases it and tries to stop it with his foot. But it is in contact with the ropes. Boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Just short of first slip! Tossed up, on off. Shanto gets the outside edge but it drops inches short of first slip.
Darted down the leg side. Shanto misses the flick.
Loopy ball, outside off. Islam gets the inside edge to square leg for one.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Shanto punches it past covers for three runs.
Full and on the pads. Worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and down the leg side. The keeper fails to gather and the batters get two byes.
Loopy ball, down the leg side. Islam leaves it.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Hit hard! Tossed up, down the leg side. Shanto sweeps it to the left of deep backward square leg for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Shanto taps it towards point for one.
Islam gets the outside edge while looking to block but it drops short of second slip.
OUT! TAKEN! RASH SHOT! Short ball, outside off. Shadman Islam goes back to cut but the ball bounces a bit more and gets the top edge. It loops up to point and Hasan Ali takes it.
Howout: c Hasan Ali b Sajid Khan

Commentary: Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Shanto works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, around off. Shanto pushes it to cover.
Loopy ball, lands on off and turns and bounces. Shanto works it with soft hands to short leg.
Flatter ball, on off. Shanto gets the inside edge past short leg for one.
Full and on middle. Worked past square leg for one.

OUT! RUN OUT! Poor work by Bangladesh. Loopy ball, on off. Haque pushes it to covers and takes off for a quick single. There is no need to take a risk like this just before Tea. Hasan Ali charges to the ball and fires a direct hit at the bowler's end. The TV umpire is called in and Mominul Haque is miles short of the crease! That also brings Tea on Day 4!
Tossed up on middle. Pushed to mid on.
Shorter length around off. Shanto blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller this time on off. Pushed to mid off.
Sharp turn around off. Shanto leaves it alone.
Tossed up nicely around off. Shanto presses forward to defend. But the ball turns away sharply with bounce. The ball misses his blade and deflects off Rizwan's gloves for two byes behind the stumps.
An arm ball on middle. Defended off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle. Rahim defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
Shorter length and around off. Rahim punches it off the back foot to backward point.
Tossed up on off. Blocked off the front foot.
Fuller around leg. Rahim sweeps it to fine leg for a single.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Nicely tossed up on off. Shanto presses forward to defend but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. The ball brushes off the pads of Rizwan and goes past first slip to third man. The batters take a couple.

NOT OUT! Sharp turn there! Sajid Khan bowls this around off. Mushfiqur Rahim stays on the back foot and looks to play it but the ball turns in sharply. He hits him high on his pads. There is a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Pakistan take the review and the Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on impact. So Mushfiqur Rahim survives!
FOUR! Short and outside off. Cut away to point for a boundary.

OUT! What was he thinking there? Mushfiqur Rahim departs now! What an anti-climax! Tossed up on off. Mushfiqur Rahim gets in his knees and slog-sweeps it. But finds the fielder at mid-wicket. Fawad Alam takes a sharp catch and Bangladesh are sinking further and that was a poor shot by Rahim. The shot selection by Rahim is quite surprising here!
Howout: c Fawad Alam b Sajid Khan

Commentary: On middle and leg turning down the leg. Das lets it go.
Shorter length on middle. Das works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Tossed up on off. Liton Das sweeps and sweeps well to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller on middle. Shanto sweeps it to deep square leg for a couple.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Another boundary and Bangladesh are not holding back here! Tossed up on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto skips down the track and smashes it straight back past the bowler for a boundary

NO BALL! Najmul Hossain Shanto survives! Fuller ball down the leg. Shanto looks to sweep it but gets a faint edge of his gloves to the keeper. The umpire has given that out. But Najmul Hossain Shanto reviews and the replays show that Nauman Ali has overstepped. So Najmul Hossain Shanto gets a lifeline and Nauman Ali has to wait further for his first wicket.
Tossed up on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller again on middle. Shanto sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Quicker on off. Defended off the back foot.

Shanto survives an LBW appeal! Tossed up, outside off. He offers his pads and there is an appeal for LBW. The impact doesn't matter but what matters is whether the ball is hitting the stumps and it isn't.
Flatter and coming in with an angle.Shanto plays it off the back foot.
Fuller on off.Shanto gets forward and defends it off the front foot.
Quicker on off. Shanto pushes it to the off side.
Another flatter delivery on middle. Shanto gets back and blocks it.
Nicely tossed up around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto presses forward to defend but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade as it turns away sharply.
Loopy ball, lands on off and turns away. Das is beaten as he looks to block.
Beaten! Full ball, lands on off and turns away sharply. It goes just past the outside edge and the off pole.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Liton Das tries to nudge it off his pads, The ball hits his pads and goes towards short fine leg.
Loopy ball, around off. Das comes forward and blocks it.
Darted on the pads. Worked past short fine leg for a couple.
Full and on off. Hit down towards the bowler. Khan gets his hand to it but it goes to long on for one.
Full on off. Worked to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Oh, dear! What is the game plan by Bangladesh here? They are trying to score runs quickly and now are in big, big trouble. Tossed up, on off. Das comes down the track and hits it straight back to the bowler. Das takes it with ease.
Full and on the pads. Swept to fine leg for a couple.
Swept again to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Shanto blocks it from the front foot.
Shakib Al Hasan gets down the track and whips it over mid on for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off. Shakib looks to work it away but gets the leading edge towards the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Risky run! Shakib pushes it to mid off and sets off for a run. The fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end. Had he hit, Shakib Al Hasan would have been walking back to the hut.
Swept to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Hit hard! Tossed up, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan sweeps it to the mid-wicket fence.
FOUR! Just over! Shanto hits it just over mid on for a boundary.
Full and on the pads. Flicked past mid-wicket for a couple.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter and on off. Blocked away.

OUT! LBW! A 5-wicket haul for Sajid Khan and the game has progressed so fast in the last hour or so! Flatter and quicker. Lands outside off and comes back in. Shanto looks to work it away but gets hit on the pads. The finger goes up but he reviews it thinking that the height could save him. But it doesn't as the Ball Tracker shows three reds! Mehidy Hasan walks out to bat.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and outside off. Pushed past mid off for one.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Hasan blocks it.
Full and on the pads. Blocked from the crease.
On off, defended.
Tossed up, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Shakib Al Hasan is not holding back! Tossed up on off, Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and smashes it wide of mid off for a boundary.
On the pads, worked away to mid-wicket for a single. Slight mix up there but no damage done in the end.
Flatter delivery on off. Defended off the back foot.

OUT! BOWLED! Another one bites the dust! Tossed up around off. Mehidy Hasan goes for a big slog sweep but misses it completely. The ball turns in and shatters the stumps. Bangladesh are looking all at sea now. This is a shocking batting display.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Beaten! Tossed up around off. Taijul Islam looks to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten as the ball turns away sharply.
Tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and works it to mid off.
Quicker this time on off. Blocked by Shakib.
Fuller on middle. Pushed to long on for a single.
Nicely tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Slower in the air around middle and leg. Islam plays it to short fine leg.
Quicker delivery outside off. Taijul Islam looks to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten.
Quicker and shorter on off. Pushed to short cover.
This time slower through the air on off. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and gets an outside edge to the off side as he looks to defend.
Shorter length, around off. Hasan pushes it to covers and wants a single but is sent back by his partner.
Drifting on leg this time. Hasan looks to work it away but gets hit on his pads. Going down the leg.
Fuller ball, on middle. Hasan sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, on off. Islam looks to defend it but gets hit on the pads and towards silly point.
Darted towards middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan looks to clip it but the ball hits his pads and goes towards short leg.
Shorter length and keeps a tad low, on off.  Shakib Al Hasan punches this ball towards the right of the bowler.
Shorter length, on off. Punched back to the left of the bowler.
Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and clips it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller delivery. Nudged to left of short fine leg.
Fuller on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and works it square on the on side for a single.
Flatter ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, wide outside off. Shakib Al Hasan goes for the sweep but misses.
Full ball, on off. Shakib gets the outside edge towards first slip.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Shakib blocks it.
Short ball, outside off. Cut away to deep point for one.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, around off. Islam gets the outside edge but it drops short of first slip.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Afridi starts with a wayward ball, down leg. Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone.
This is a full ball, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan looks for a booming drive but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, nipping back in down leg. Shakib Al Hasan misses his nudge on the leg side.
Back of a length, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan stays back and eases it back past the bowler towards mid on.
Afridi bangs it into the deck, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan ducks underneath watchfully. A maiden over from Shaheen Afridi to start with.
Tossed up, around leg. Taijul Islam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Turn and bounce! Floated, around off and spinning away late. Taijul Islam looks to defend but the ball spins past his blade.
Flatter ball, on off. Taijul Islam looks to defend but he gets an outside edge towards first slip, on the bounce.
Fuller in length, on off. Taijul Islam blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Taijul Islam prods but sways away from the line of the ball.
OUT! LBW! Sajid Khan strikes straightaway! Flatter ball, on middle, going on with the angle from middle. Taijul Islam looks to defend but he misses and gets rapped on his pads.

NOT OUT! Leg bye! Shakib Al Hasan survives! Full ball, niiping back in from middle. Shakib Al Hasan looks to dig it out but he misses and gets hit low on his pad. Shaheen Afridi appeals but the umpire says no. Babar Azam takes a review but the Ball Tracker confirms that the ball would have gone down leg so the on-field decision stays and Pakistan lose a reveiw. The batters sneak in a leg bye.
Good-length delivery around off and angling across the batter. Khaled Ahmed plays it inside the line of the ball. Superb bowling this by Shaheen Afridi.
OUT! BOWLED! Top delivery from Shaheen Afridi! A yorker, around off. Khaled Ahmed looks to block but he misses and the ball crashes onto his sticks.
Banged in short, around off. Ebadot Hossain ducks under it.
Length ball, outside off. Ebadot Hossain leaves it alone.
Full ball, outside off. Ebadot Hossain lets it be.
Tossed up, on off. Shakib Al Hasan heaves it to deep mid-wicket but does not take the single.
Flatter ball, on off. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan punches it to cover.
Flatter ball, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan cuts it to deep cover and takes the single this time.
Tossed up, around off. Ebadot Hossain defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, turning in from off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it off the back foot.
A full ball, on off. Shakib Al Hasan heaves it across the line to wide long on.
A brilliant yorker on middle this time. Shakib Al Hasan just manages to dig it out towards the off side.
Drifting on the pads this time. Hasan clips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
A yorker, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan looks to dig it out but he misses and the ball sneaks through his bat towards the keeper.
A low full toss, around off. Shakib Al Hasan drags it to mid off and takes a single.
Another yorker, just outside off. Ebadot Hossain looks to block but he misses as the ball goes past his blade.
Flatter ball, on off. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Shadman Islam squeezes it out to mid off.
Flatter ball, around off. Shakib Al Hasan stays back and cuts it past the point fielder for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, around off. Shakib Al Hasan works it to wide of long off for a run.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Tossed up, around middle. Shakib Al Hasan backs away and carves it past the cover fielder for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Sajid Khan takes the last wicket and he finishes with eight wickets to his name! Flatter ball, around off. Shakib Al Hasan skips down to go over extra cover but he fails to get the elevation and hits it straight to Azhar Ali at cover who takes a sharp catch. Bangladesh are bundled out for 87 and Pakistan have imposed the follow-on.
Howout: c Azhar Ali b Sajid Khan

Commentary: A Jaffa to start with! Good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel and curling away late. Shadman Islam looks to defend but the ball goes past his blade.
Length ball, on off. Shadman Islam blocks it watchfully off the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Shadman Islam leaves it alone.
Full ball, way outside off. Shadman Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball, around middle. Shadman Islam blocks it towards cover-point without any feet movement.
Length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam lets it be.
FOUR! Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Bangladesh are underway! Ali serves a half-volley, on the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards the vacant fine leg region for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out.
Fuller in length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy clips it to fine leg and collects a run.
Short of a length, outside off. Shadman Islam lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball, nipping in from outside off. Shadman Islam shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam leaves it alone.
Full ball, around leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR BYES! A very wayward ball, down leg. Shadman Islam lets it be. Mohammad Rizwan behind the sticks dives to his right but the ball goes past him into the fine leg fence.
Another ball, down leg. Shadman Islam misses his flick.
Length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam leaves it alone.
Full ball, way outside off and shaping away late. Shadman Islam presses forward but does not offer any shot to this one.
Full ball, darted on the pads. Shadman Islam clips it past the mid-wicket fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Length ball, angling in from middle and leg and going down leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy misses his flick.

OUT! BOWLED! Hasan Ali strikes and Bangladesh lose their first wicket! Length ball, just outside off and nipping back in, Mahmudul Hasan Joy prods and looks to drive through covers but the ball sneaks through his bat and crashes onto his off pole. Hasan Ali is elated!
Length ball, around middle and shaping away a bit. Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Full ball, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to block but it goes off the outer half of the bat towards slip cordon.
Good-length ball, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it out. A wicket-maiden from Hasan Ali!

OUT! LBW! Both the openers are back into the hut now! A length delivery on off and nips back in sharply. Shohidul Islam looks to defend it but misses. The ball hits his pads and Afridi appeals. The umpire raises his finger and Shaheen Afridi is elated. Bangladesh are in real trouble now.
Almost squared him up! Full ball and angling into middle. Haque looks to work it away towards the on side but gets a leading edge towards the off side.
Good-length delivery and around off. Haque decides to leave it alone.
A full ball, on off this time. Mominul Haque defends this off the front foot.
A good bouncer this time angling into the body. Mominul Haque ducks under it.
In the air...but safe! A length ball, on off. Mominul Haque is early in his drive and gets the bottom of his blade towards covers aerially for a single.
FOUR! Classy shot! Overpitched delivery and outside off. Mominul Haque leans forward and drives it beautifully through cover-point for a boundary.
On the pads this time. Haque clips it to mid-wicket for a couple.

OUT! LBW! The skipper departs now! A length ball, on off. The ball came back in sharply from the angle. Mominul Haque looks to defend this off the front foot but misses. The ball hits his pads and Pakistan players appeal. The umpire raises his finger but Mominul Haque reviews it. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that it is pad first. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows three reds. So Mominul Haque has to walk back and Bangladesh lose their third wicket.
A good-length delivery and around off. Rahim leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Rahim defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
A length ball on off again. Defended by Rahim towards point.
A good-length delivery and outside off. Shanto looks to poke at it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
FOUR! A glorious drive this time! Overpitched around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto leans forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Full ball, on off. Driven to mid on this time.
A good-length delivery on off. Shanto pushes at it with soft hands and gets it past backward point for a couple.
On a length, on off. Defended solidly off the front foot towards the off side.
A length ball and angling into middle. Shanto taps it towards the on side as fielder at short leg stops it with a dive.
A full ball angling into off pole. Rahim pushes it off the front foot and gets a thick outside edge to gully.
Back of a length, on off. Defended off the back foot.
A length ball, outside off. Rahim leaves it alone this time.
A full ball and angling into middle and leg. Rahim looks to work it away but gets a leading edge towards the off side.
A length ball, on middle. Rahim defends it off the front foot towards the on side.
A full ball, on middle and leg again. Rahim clips it to mid-wicket.

OUT! Caught! Another one bites the dust! Back of a length delivery on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto pokes at it tentatively and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies off his blade to gully and Fawad Alam there takes a sharp catch. Bangladesh are four down with almost nothing on the board! The Bangladesh top order is again back into the hut cheaply.
Howout: c Fawad Alam b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Beaten! A good-length delivery and angling across the batter. Das looks to defend it but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.

Another jaffa! A good-length delivery around off. Das looks to defend it again but the ball misses the outside edge of his blade by a whisker again. He is getting it to bounce off the length. Brilliant stuff!
A short ball this time, on middle. Liton Das ducks under it this time.
Full ball and angling across. Das leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Defended off the back foot towards the off side.
Length ball, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim nudges it to square leg and collects a run.
Good-length delivery, around off. Liton Das blocks it off the front foot.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Liton Das pushes it to mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off. Liton Das stays back and punches it to backward point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Liton Das leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off, staying a touch low. Liton Das stays back to block but he misses as the ball goes under his bat.
Flatter ball, on off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out.
BEATEN! Tossed up, around off and turning away late. Mushfiqur Rahim prods to block but the ball spins past his blade.
Fuller in length, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, down leg. Mushfiqur Rahim gets down on his knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for a run.
Flatter ball, on off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, around off. Liton Das hangs back and punches it to backward point.
Length ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off, nipping in late. Mushfiqur Rahim sways away from the line of the ball.
Good-length delivery, just outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim stays back and lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around leg. Mushfiqur Rahim tucks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pad and the ball dabs onto the deck. A maiden over from Faheem Ashraf!
Tossed up, around middle. Liton Das blocks it out.
Flatter ball, around middle. Liton Das tucks it towards the short leg fielder.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Liton Das blocks it out.
Fuller in length, around middle. Liton Das prods and works it to mid on.
Flatter ball, outside off. Liton Das stays back and cuts it to backward point.
Tossed up, around off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim presses forward but lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone watchfully.
Short of a length, angling in from outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend but he gets the inside edge onto his pad.

A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! A length ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim prods and looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Faheem Ashraf appeals but the impact was way outside off.
Short of a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim stays back and blocks it to cover.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Das gets back and defends it.
Fuller on middle this time. Driven to mid off this time.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shorter in length and turning away. Liton Das lets it turn and then works it away towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Drifting on the pads this time. Das nudges it to deep mid-wicket leg for a couple.
Shorter in length and turning away from middle. Das gets on the back foot and whips it away towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
On a length, around off. Rahim defends this solidly off the back foot towards the off side.
A length ball again, on off. Rahim gets forward and defends it square on the off side.
A Fuller ball and wider outside off. Rahim leaves it alone comfortably.
On a length and wide outside off again. Rahim leaves it alone again.
Faheem Ashraf again bowls this full and wide outside off. Rahim decides to not touch it.
Same line and same result. A length ball, outside off. Rahim lets it go.
Quicker and flatter on off. Das defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
Tossed up this time on off. Das defends this off the front foot.
Another loopy delivery on off. Defended off the front foot towards the off side.
An arm ball angling into off. Das blocks it off the back foot.
In the air...but safe! Tossed up around off. Liton Das looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball falls just short of the point fielder.
Fuller on off. Driven through covers for a couple. This is what he tried to do in the previous ball also.
Drifting down the leg side this time. Rahim looks to flick it but misses as it is way down the leg side.
A full ball, around off. Rahim drives it to covers.
A full ball on middle this time. Rahim pushes it to mid on this time.
Very full on middle this time. Almost a yorker! Rahim blocks it out in the end.
A length ball, on off. Nips back in a little. Rahim looks to defend it off the front foot and gets the inner half of his blade towards the on side.
A length delivery and outside off. Rahim leaves it alone. Faheem Ashraf completes his fourth maiden in a row!

BEATEN! Nicley tossed up on middle. Liton Das presses forward to defend but the ball turns away and misses the outside edge of his blade. The replays now show that there was a spike of his blade on UltraEdge but Pakistan did not appeal.
FOUR! Poor ball and punished! A short ball, on off. Liton Das rocks back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. Defended off the front foot.
Fuller on off. Das drives it to covers.
A fuller ball again. Defended off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Das blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim cuts it to wide of point and takes a couple.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim pushes it to mid off for a run.
Tossed up, around off. Liton Das blocks it out.
FOUR! In the air...but just wide of the mid-wicket fielder! Tossed up, around off. Liton Das skips down and heaves it to wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! Liton Das is on the charge! Fuller in length, on middle. Das shimmies down and tonks it to wide of mid on and bags another boundary.
Tossed up, on middle. Liton Das eases it to mid on for one.
Flatter ball, around off. Liton Das blocks it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Liton Das drives hard to the cover fielder who fumbles and the batters take a run.
Flatter ball, around middle. Rahim defends it off the front foot.
On a length, around middle. Liton Das prods and keeps it out.
A tad short, outside off. Liton Das stays back and cuts it to extra cover for a single.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg for a run.
Flatter ball, on off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out.
FOUR! The runs have started to flow now for Bangladesh. This is a half-tracker, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim stays back and pulls it along the ground behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! Tossed up, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim skips down and carves it past the mid off fielder for a boundary.
Tossed up, around middle. Mushfiqur Rahim tucks it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, around leg. Mushfiqur Rahim turns it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, outside off. Liton Das drives it to extra cover and collects a single.
FOUR BYES! Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone and the ball stays low to go past the keeper. The ball races away to the fence.
On a length, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim pushes it to wide of cover and takes off a run.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Liton Das drives it to wide of deep cover and takes a single.
Flighted delivery, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim eases it to mid on. That will be Lunch on Day 5.
FOUR! Liton Das starts the session with a boundary! Shorter in length on middle and leg. Liton Das rocks back and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off. Das gets across and defends it off the back foot.
Shorter again on middle and leg. Das pulls it to the fielder at deep square leg this time.
Tossed up on off. Rahim defends this off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Rahim dabs it to the on side.
