Tossed up on off. Rahim looks to sweep but misses and gets rapped up on the pads. But the impact is outside off.
A length ball, on off. Das defends this off the back foot.

FOUR! Another boundary for Liton Das! Drifting on the pads this time and Liton Das clips this off his pads towards deep square leg for a boundary. Sloppy fielding in the deep there and that rolls towards the fence.
On a length, on off. Das looks to leave it at the last moment but gets the underedge of his blade back to the keeper.
On a length , on off. Das blocks it out.
Angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Nudged to mid-wicket.
On a length, on off. Defended solidly off the back foot.
Shorter in length on off. Rahim rocks back and punches it through covers for a couple.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Pushed to mid on..
Tossed up on off. Rahim defends this off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Rahim pushes it off the front foot towards mid off.
Sharp turn and bounce! Tossed up around off. Rahim goes on the back foot and looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but no damage done.
On middle and leg. Clipped to square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on leg. Rahim tucks it to square leg for a single.
Short ball and outside off. Das lets it go this time.

Another short ball from 'round the wicket. This time it is angled into the body. Liton Das sways away from the line of the ball and the ball just misses his gloves by a whisker. They think of a review but decide going against it in the end.
Short ball again and this time down the leg side. Das ducks under it.
Short again on off this time. Das jumps and just pushes it uppishly towards deep backward point for a single.
Shaheen Afridi ends the over with another short ball. Mushfiqur Rahim ducks under it comfortably.
Around off and turning in. Das gets across and looks to tuck it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Shorter length again, on middle. Das tucks it to fine leg for a single.
On off and turning in. Rahim defends this off the back foot.
Shorter length around off. Rahim pushes it off the back foot to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up on off. Driven to covers.
Again fuller and around off. Das drives it again to the fielder at covers.
A length ball and outside off. Rahim leaves it alone.
A good bouncer this time, on middle. Rahim ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle and some extra bounce there. Rahim looks to defend and gets it off the handle of his blade towards the on side.
Back of a length and outside off. Rahim decides to let it go.
A good-length delivery and angling across. Mushfiqur Rahim tries to poke at it as the ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
A length ball, on off. Rahim defends this solidly off the back foot.

OUT! TAKEN! Liton Das has thrown it away and he stands in disbelief! A half-tracker, around off. Liton Das stays back and looks to pull hard but he hits it straight to Fawad Alam at square leg who juggles it but takes it in the end. A much-needed breakthrough for Pakistan and they are delighted! Bangladesh lose their fifth wicket and are in deep trouble now!
Howout: c Fawad Alam b Sajid Khan

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh, dear! Mushfiqur Rahim gets out just at the stroke of Tea and he would be absolutely gutted with himself! This is a huge moment in the context of this game and it is surely a body blow for Bangladesh. This was needless from Rahim and it could cost Bangladesh in the end. It was a flatter ball, on middle. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it to mid-wicket and goes for a run. Abdullah Shafique at mid-wicket collects the ball cleanly and throws it to the keeper Mohammad Rizwan who whips the bails off. Mushfiqur Rahim puts in a dive but his bat bounced off the ground and wasn't grounded before Rizwan took the bails off. The TV umpire has a good look at it and gives it out in the end. Mushfiqur Rahim walks back in anger and that will be Tea on Day 5.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan departs and Pakistan's skipper strikes! Fuller ball, on off, Mehidy Hasan looks to sweep it but misses. He gets rapped up on the pads and there is a huge appeal. But the umpire is unmoved. Babar Azam takes the review straightaway. The replays roll in and it shows no bat on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracker rolls in now and it shows three reds. Mehidy Hasan has to walk back. First wicket for Babar Azam in Test cricket. What a move by Babar Azam to bring himself into the attack! Pakistan BELIEVE!

OUT! LBW! There it is! Sajid Khan gets yet another wicket and does the job for his side! What a Test match this has proved to be! This was a flatter ball, around middle and going on with the angle. Taijul Islam stays back to block but he misses and gets rapped on the pads. Sajid Khan appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Ebadot Hossain at the non-striker's end asks his partner to review it immediately. Islam obliges but the Ball tracker indicates three reds and Taijul Islam is a goner! Pakistani players are over the moon! Pakistan WIN THE MATCH BY AN INNINGS AND 8 RUNS!
